cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use CIMA, please cite the archived Zenodo record."
title: "CIMA: Bounded, Traceable, and Navigable Memory for Language Model Systems"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Fuentes"
    given-names: "Alberto"
year: 2026
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.20465483"
url: "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20465483"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Berloe/cima-demonstrator"
version: "1.0-rc2"
license: "MIT"
abstract: >-
  CIMA is a specification and demonstrator for governed, bounded, traceable,
  and navigable memory/context construction in LLM-based systems. It separates
  stored memory from active context, preserves lineage from context markers to
  source spans, and constrains publication through prompt-visible evidence
  markers or traceable abstention. The published demonstrator evaluates
  structural lineage and publication properties; it does not claim semantic
  entailment, factuality guarantees, or complete agent-runtime functionality.
keywords:
  - LLM memory
  - context engineering
  - provenance
  - auditability
  - traceability
  - governed memory
